# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Extra PACS nodes for redundancy / long-term (28yr) retention.
#
# How it works:
#   • Every study is sent (C-STORE) to the primary PACS *and* every
#     fallback node configured here.
#   • A study is only marked "sent" once ALL nodes confirm storage,
#     so a node that is briefly offline is retried automatically.
#   • Sends are idempotent — re-sending the same study just merges.
#
# To use:
#   1. Copy this file to ".env"   (cp pacs-nodes.env.example .env)
#   2. Fill in the IP / port / AE title for each fallback site.
#   3. Redeploy:  ./deploy.sh
#
# The primary PACS is the local Orthanc container and is configured
# in docker-compose.yml (PACS_HOST/PACS_PORT/PACS_AET) — no need to
# touch it here.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Secondary PACS (fallback site #1) ──
PACS2_HOST=192.168.1.50
PACS2_PORT=104
PACS2_AET=BACKUP_PACS

# ── Tertiary PACS (fallback site #2) ──
# PACS3_HOST=10.0.0.20
# PACS3_PORT=11112
# PACS3_AET=ARCHIVE_PACS

# You can keep going up to PACS9_* using the same pattern:
#   PACS4_HOST / PACS4_PORT / PACS4_AET ... PACS9_*
